article.headline: S. Illinois 86, SE Missouri 65
article.story: CAPE GIRARDEAU, Mo. -- Tony Freeman scored 26 points to lead Southern Illinois to an 86-65 win against Southeast Missouri on Wednesday. Freeman made 10 of 15 field goals, including 6 of 11 3-pointers, for the Salukis (4-2). Anthony Booker added 10 points and 11 rebounds for Southern Illinois. Nick Evans scored 15, and Carlton Fay and Kevin Dillard had 11 apiece. Anthony Allison led Southeast Missouri (3-7) with 15 points. Eric McCrary scored 13, and LaMont Russell grabbed 10 rebounds. Southern Illinois used a 25-5 run to take a 40-14 lead with about three minutes left in the first half. The Salukis shot 56.1 percent from the field, including 42.1 percent on 3-pointers, and scored 27 points off turnovers.
